#. <section class="sutta" id="mn8"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn8:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 8"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 8"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn8:0.2"
msgid "Sallekhasutta"
msgstr "Self-Effacement"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn8:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā mahācundo sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā mahācundo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Mahācunda came out of retreat and went "
"to the Buddha. He bowed, sat down to one side, and said to the Buddha:"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:3.1"
msgid "“yā imā, bhante, anekavihitā diṭṭhiyo loke uppajjanti—"
msgstr "“Sir, there are many different views that arise in the world"

msgctxt "mn8:3.2"
msgid "attavādapaṭisaṃyuttā vā lokavādapaṭisaṃyuttā vā—"
msgstr "connected with doctrines of the self or with doctrines of the cosmos."

# This question is a little curiously phrased in the Pali, and I suspect some corruption. The idiom adimeva occurs several times in the Samyutta (SN 47.15, etc.), where it refers to a mendicant purifying the “starting point” of kusala dhamma, i.e. sila and ditthi. Since ditthi are also spoken of here, the context must be the same. Thus BB following the comm errs in inserting “meditative training” here, as this “adi” is specifically said to precede meditation, as indeed it does in this sutta. (Neither MA 91 nor EA 47.9 appears to have close parallel to this phrase) This is just the start of the comm’s systematic misinterpretation of this sutta. Further, the question must be “how” this is done, as that is the answer the Buddha gives. Both Chinese texts have 云何 here, which typically stands for katham = how?
msgctxt "mn8:3.3"
msgid ""
"ādimeva nu kho, bhante, bhikkhuno manasikaroto evametāsaṃ diṭṭhīnaṃ pahānaṃ "
"hoti, evametāsaṃ diṭṭhīnaṃ paṭinissaggo hotī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"How does a mendicant who is focusing on the starting point give up and let "
"go of these views?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:3.4"
msgid "“Yā imā, cunda, anekavihitā diṭṭhiyo loke uppajjanti—"
msgstr "“Cunda, there are many different views that arise in the world"

msgctxt "mn8:3.5"
msgid "attavādapaṭisaṃyuttā vā lokavādapaṭisaṃyuttā vā—"
msgstr "connected with doctrines of the self or with doctrines of the cosmos."

msgctxt "mn8:3.6"
msgid ""
"yattha cetā diṭṭhiyo uppajjanti yattha ca anusenti yattha ca samudācaranti "
"taṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na me so attā’ti—evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññā passato evametāsaṃ diṭṭhīnaṃ pahānaṃ hoti, evametāsaṃ diṭṭhīnaṃ "
"paṭinissaggo hoti."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant gives up and lets go of these views by truly seeing with right "
"wisdom where they arise, where they settle in, and where they operate as: ‘"
"This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.41"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:4.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ idhekacco bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi "
"vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ "
"paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihareyya."
msgstr ""
"It’s possible that a certain mendicant, quite secluded from sensual "
"pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, might enter and remain in the "
"first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while "
"placing the mind and keeping it connected."

msgctxt "mn8:4.2"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They might think"

msgctxt "mn8:4.3"
msgid "‘sallekhena viharāmī’ti."
msgstr "they’re practicing self-effacement."

msgctxt "mn8:4.4"
msgid "Na kho panete, cunda, ariyassa vinaye sallekhā vuccanti."
msgstr ""
"But in the training of the noble one these are not called ‘self-effacement’;"

msgctxt "mn8:4.5"
msgid "Diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārā ete ariyassa vinaye vuccanti."
msgstr "they’re called ‘blissful meditations in the present life’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:5.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ idhekacco bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ "
"vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ "
"samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihareyya."
msgstr ""
"It’s possible that some mendicant, as the placing of the mind and keeping it "
"connected are stilled, might enter and remain in the second absorption, "
"which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and "
"confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it "
"connected."

msgctxt "mn8:5.2"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They might think"

msgctxt "mn8:5.3"
msgid "‘sallekhena viharāmī’ti."
msgstr "they’re practicing self-effacement."

msgctxt "mn8:5.4"
msgid "Na kho panete, cunda, ariyassa vinaye sallekhā vuccanti."
msgstr ""
"But in the training of the noble one these are not called ‘self-effacement’;"

msgctxt "mn8:5.5"
msgid "Diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārā ete ariyassa vinaye vuccanti."
msgstr "they’re called ‘blissful meditations in the present life’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:6.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ idhekacco bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā "
"upekkhako ca vihareyya, sato ca sampajāno sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeyya, "
"yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja vihareyya."
msgstr ""
"It’s possible that some mendicant, with the fading away of rapture, might "
"enter and remain in the third absorption, where they meditate with "
"equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which "
"the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’"

msgctxt "mn8:6.2"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They might think"

msgctxt "mn8:6.3"
msgid "‘sallekhena viharāmī’ti."
msgstr "they’re practicing self-effacement."

msgctxt "mn8:6.4"
msgid "Na kho panete, cunda, ariyassa vinaye sallekhā vuccanti."
msgstr ""
"But in the training of the noble one these are not called ‘self-effacement’;"

msgctxt "mn8:6.5"
msgid "Diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārā ete ariyassa vinaye vuccanti."
msgstr "they’re called ‘blissful meditations in the present life’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:7.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ idhekacco bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā "
"dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ "
"upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihareyya."
msgstr ""
"It’s possible that some mendicant, with the giving up of pleasure and pain, "
"and the ending of former happiness and sadness, might enter and remain in "
"the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and "
"mindfulness."

msgctxt "mn8:7.2"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They might think"

msgctxt "mn8:7.3"
msgid "‘sallekhena viharāmī’ti."
msgstr "they’re practicing self-effacement."

msgctxt "mn8:7.4"
msgid "Na kho panete, cunda, ariyassa vinaye sallekhā vuccanti."
msgstr ""
"But in the training of the noble one these are not called ‘self-effacement’;"

msgctxt "mn8:7.5"
msgid "Diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārā ete ariyassa vinaye vuccanti."
msgstr "they’re called ‘blissful meditations in the present life’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:8.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ idhekacco bhikkhu sabbaso "
"rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā, paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā, nānattasaññānaṃ "
"amanasikārā, ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja vihareyya."
msgstr ""
"It’s possible that some mendicant, going totally beyond perceptions of form, "
"with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions "
"of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, might enter and remain in the "
"dimension of infinite space."

msgctxt "mn8:8.2"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They might think"

msgctxt "mn8:8.3"
msgid "‘sallekhena viharāmī’ti."
msgstr "they’re practicing self-effacement."

msgctxt "mn8:8.4"
msgid "Na kho panete, cunda, ariyassa vinaye sallekhā vuccanti."
msgstr ""
"But in the training of the noble one these are not called ‘self-effacement’;"

msgctxt "mn8:8.5"
msgid "Santā ete vihārā ariyassa vinaye vuccanti."
msgstr "they’re called ‘peaceful meditations’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:9.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ idhekacco bhikkhu sabbaso "
"ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ "
"upasampajja vihareyya."
msgstr ""
"It’s possible that some mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of "
"infinite space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, might enter and "
"remain in the dimension of infinite consciousness."

msgctxt "mn8:9.2"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They might think"

msgctxt "mn8:9.3"
msgid "‘sallekhena viharāmī’ti."
msgstr "they’re practicing self-effacement."

msgctxt "mn8:9.4"
msgid "Na kho panete, cunda, ariyassa vinaye sallekhā vuccanti."
msgstr ""
"But in the training of the noble one these are not called ‘self-effacement’;"

msgctxt "mn8:9.5"
msgid "Santā ete vihārā ariyassa vinaye vuccanti."
msgstr "they’re called ‘peaceful meditations’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:10.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ idhekacco bhikkhu sabbaso "
"viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja "
"vihareyya."
msgstr ""
"It’s possible that some mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of "
"infinite consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, might enter "
"and remain in the dimension of nothingness."

msgctxt "mn8:10.2"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They might think"

msgctxt "mn8:10.3"
msgid "‘sallekhena viharāmī’ti."
msgstr "they’re practicing self-effacement."

msgctxt "mn8:10.4"
msgid "Na kho panete, cunda, ariyassa vinaye sallekhā vuccanti."
msgstr ""
"But in the training of the noble one these are not called ‘self-effacement’;"

msgctxt "mn8:10.5"
msgid "Santā ete vihārā ariyassa vinaye vuccanti."
msgstr "they’re called ‘peaceful meditations’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.42"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:11.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ idhekacco bhikkhu sabbaso "
"ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja vihareyya."
msgstr ""
"It’s possible that some mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of "
"nothingness, might enter and remain in the dimension of neither perception "
"nor non-perception."

msgctxt "mn8:11.2"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They might think"

msgctxt "mn8:11.3"
msgid "‘sallekhena viharāmī’ti."
msgstr "they’re practicing self-effacement."

msgctxt "mn8:11.4"
msgid "Na kho panete, cunda, ariyassa vinaye sallekhā vuccanti."
msgstr ""
"But in the training of the noble one these are not called ‘self-effacement’;"

msgctxt "mn8:11.5"
msgid "Santā ete vihārā ariyassa vinaye vuccanti."
msgstr "they’re called ‘peaceful meditations’."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "mn8:11.6"
msgid "1. Sallekhapariyāya"
msgstr "1. The Exposition of Self-Effacement"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.1"
msgid "Idha kho pana vo, cunda, sallekho karaṇīyo."
msgstr ""
"Now, Cunda, you should work on self-effacement in each of the following ways."

# The idiom here with “sallekho karaniyo” is strikingly reminiscent of the sekhiyas in the Vinaya, each of which ends with sikkha karaniya
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.2"
msgid ""
"‘Pare vihiṃsakā bhavissanti, mayamettha avihiṃsakā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (1)"
msgstr "‘Others will be cruel, but here we will not be cruel.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.3"
msgid ""
"‘Pare pāṇātipātī bhavissanti, mayamettha pāṇātipātā paṭiviratā bhavissāmā’ti "
"sallekho karaṇīyo. (2)"
msgstr ""
"‘Others will kill living creatures, but here we will not kill living "
"creatures.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.4"
msgid ""
"‘Pare adinnādāyī bhavissanti, mayamettha adinnādānā paṭiviratā bhavissāmā’ti "
"sallekho karaṇīyo. (3)"
msgstr "‘Others will steal, but here we will not steal.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.5"
msgid ""
"‘Pare abrahmacārī bhavissanti, mayamettha brahmacārī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (4)"
msgstr "‘Others will be unchaste, but here we will not be unchaste.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.6"
msgid ""
"‘Pare musāvādī bhavissanti, mayamettha musāvādā paṭiviratā bhavissāmā’ti "
"sallekho karaṇīyo. (5)"
msgstr "‘Others will lie, but here we will not lie.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
#. VAR: pisuṇavācā → pisuṇāvācā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn8:12.7"
msgid ""
"‘Pare pisuṇavācā bhavissanti, mayamettha pisuṇāya vācāya paṭiviratā "
"bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (6)"
msgstr "‘Others will speak divisively, but here we will not speak divisively.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
#. VAR: pharusavācā → pharusāvācā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn8:12.8"
msgid ""
"‘Pare pharusavācā bhavissanti, mayamettha pharusāya vācāya paṭiviratā "
"bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (7)"
msgstr "‘Others will speak harshly, but here we will not speak harshly.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.9"
msgid ""
"‘Pare samphappalāpī bhavissanti, mayamettha samphappalāpā paṭiviratā "
"bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (8)"
msgstr "‘Others will talk nonsense, but here we will not talk nonsense.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.10"
msgid ""
"‘Pare abhijjhālū bhavissanti, mayamettha anabhijjhālū bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (9)"
msgstr "‘Others will be covetous, but here we will not be covetous.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.11"
msgid ""
"‘Pare byāpannacittā bhavissanti, mayamettha abyāpannacittā bhavissāmā’ti "
"sallekho karaṇīyo. (10)"
msgstr "‘Others will have ill will, but here we will not have ill will.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.12"
msgid ""
"‘Pare micchādiṭṭhī bhavissanti, mayamettha sammādiṭṭhī bhavissāmā’ti "
"sallekho karaṇīyo. (11)"
msgstr "‘Others will have wrong view, but here we will have right view.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.13"
msgid ""
"‘Pare micchāsaṅkappā bhavissanti, mayamettha sammāsaṅkappā bhavissāmā’ti "
"sallekho karaṇīyo. (12)"
msgstr "‘Others will have wrong thought, but here we will have right thought.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.14"
msgid ""
"‘Pare micchāvācā bhavissanti, mayamettha sammāvācā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (13)"
msgstr "‘Others will have wrong speech, but here we will have right speech.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.15"
msgid ""
"‘Pare micchākammantā bhavissanti, mayamettha sammākammantā bhavissāmā’ti "
"sallekho karaṇīyo. (14)"
msgstr "‘Others will have wrong action, but here we will have right action.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.16"
msgid ""
"‘Pare micchāājīvā bhavissanti, mayamettha sammāājīvā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (15)"
msgstr ""
"‘Others will have wrong livelihood, but here we will have right livelihood.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.17"
msgid ""
"‘Pare micchāvāyāmā bhavissanti, mayamettha sammāvāyāmā bhavissāmā’ti "
"sallekho karaṇīyo. (16)"
msgstr "‘Others will have wrong effort, but here we will have right effort.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.18"
msgid ""
"‘Pare micchāsatī bhavissanti, mayamettha sammāsatī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (17)"
msgstr ""
"‘Others will have wrong mindfulness, but here we will have right "
"mindfulness.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.19"
msgid ""
"‘Pare micchāsamādhi bhavissanti, mayamettha sammāsamādhī bhavissāmā’ti "
"sallekho karaṇīyo. (18)"
msgstr ""
"‘Others will have wrong immersion, but here we will have right immersion.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc30"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.20"
msgid ""
"‘Pare micchāñāṇī bhavissanti, mayamettha sammāñāṇī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (19)"
msgstr ""
"‘Others will have wrong knowledge, but here we will have right knowledge.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc31"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.21"
msgid ""
"‘Pare micchāvimuttī bhavissanti, mayamettha sammāvimuttī bhavissāmā’ti "
"sallekho karaṇīyo. (20)"
msgstr "‘Others will have wrong freedom, but here we will have right freedom.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc32"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.22"
msgid ""
"‘Pare thinamiddhapariyuṭṭhitā bhavissanti, mayamettha vigatathinamiddhā "
"bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (21)"
msgstr ""
"‘Others will be overcome with dullness and drowsiness, but here we will be "
"rid of dullness and drowsiness.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc33"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.23"
msgid ""
"‘Pare uddhatā bhavissanti, mayamettha anuddhatā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (22)"
msgstr "‘Others will be restless, but here we will not be restless.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc34"></a>
#. VAR: vicikicchī → vecikicchī (bj, s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn8:12.24"
msgid ""
"‘Pare vicikicchī bhavissanti, mayamettha tiṇṇavicikicchā bhavissāmā’ti "
"sallekho karaṇīyo. (23)"
msgstr "‘Others will have doubts, but here we will have gone beyond doubt.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc35"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.25"
msgid ""
"‘Pare kodhanā bhavissanti, mayamettha akkodhanā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (24)"
msgstr "‘Others will be angry, but here we will be without anger.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc36"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.26"
msgid ""
"‘Pare upanāhī bhavissanti, mayamettha anupanāhī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (25)"
msgstr "‘Others will be hostile, but here we will be without hostility.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.43"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc37"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.27"
msgid ""
"‘Pare makkhī bhavissanti, mayamettha amakkhī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (26)"
msgstr "‘Others will be offensive, but here we will be inoffensive.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc38"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.28"
msgid ""
"‘Pare paḷāsī bhavissanti, mayamettha apaḷāsī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (27)"
msgstr "‘Others will be contemptuous, but here we will be without contempt.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc39"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.29"
msgid ""
"‘Pare issukī bhavissanti, mayamettha anissukī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (28)"
msgstr "‘Others will be envious, but here we will be without envy.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc40"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.30"
msgid ""
"‘Pare maccharī bhavissanti, mayamettha amaccharī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (29)"
msgstr "‘Others will be stingy, but here we will be without stinginess.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc41"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.31"
msgid ""
"‘Pare saṭhā bhavissanti, mayamettha asaṭhā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. "
"(30)"
msgstr "‘Others will be devious, but here we will not be devious.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc42"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.32"
msgid ""
"‘Pare māyāvī bhavissanti, mayamettha amāyāvī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (31)"
msgstr "‘Others will be deceitful, but here we will not be deceitful.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc43"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.33"
msgid ""
"‘Pare thaddhā bhavissanti, mayamettha atthaddhā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (32)"
msgstr "‘Others will be stubborn, but here we will not be stubborn.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc44"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.34"
msgid ""
"‘Pare atimānī bhavissanti, mayamettha anatimānī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (33)"
msgstr "‘Others will be arrogant, but here we will not be arrogant.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc45"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.35"
msgid ""
"‘Pare dubbacā bhavissanti, mayamettha suvacā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (34)"
msgstr ""
"‘Others will be hard to admonish, but here we will not be hard to admonish.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc46"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.36"
msgid ""
"‘Pare pāpamittā bhavissanti, mayamettha kalyāṇamittā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (35)"
msgstr "‘Others will have bad friends, but here we will have good friends.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc47"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.37"
msgid ""
"‘Pare pamattā bhavissanti, mayamettha appamattā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (36)"
msgstr "‘Others will be negligent, but here we will be diligent.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc48"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.38"
msgid ""
"‘Pare assaddhā bhavissanti, mayamettha saddhā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (37)"
msgstr "‘Others will be faithless, but here we will have faith.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc49"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.39"
msgid ""
"‘Pare ahirikā bhavissanti, mayamettha hirimanā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (38)"
msgstr ""
"‘Others will be conscienceless, but here we will have a sense of conscience.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc50"></a>
#. VAR: anottāpī → anottappī (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "mn8:12.40"
msgid ""
"‘Pare anottāpī bhavissanti, mayamettha ottāpī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (39)"
msgstr "‘Others will be imprudent, but here we will be prudent.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc51"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.41"
msgid ""
"‘Pare appassutā bhavissanti, mayamettha bahussutā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (40)"
msgstr "‘Others will be uneducated, but here we will be well educated.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc52"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.42"
msgid ""
"‘Pare kusītā bhavissanti, mayamettha āraddhavīriyā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (41)"
msgstr "‘Others will be lazy, but here we will be energetic.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc53"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.43"
msgid ""
"‘Pare muṭṭhassatī bhavissanti, mayamettha upaṭṭhitassatī bhavissāmā’ti "
"sallekho karaṇīyo. (42)"
msgstr "‘Others will be unmindful, but here we will be mindful.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc54"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.44"
msgid ""
"‘Pare duppaññā bhavissanti, mayamettha paññāsampannā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (43)"
msgstr "‘Others will be witless, but here we will be accomplished in wisdom.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc55"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:12.45"
msgid ""
"‘Pare sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggī bhavissanti, mayamettha "
"asandiṭṭhiparāmāsī anādhānaggāhī suppaṭinissaggī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho "
"karaṇīyo. (44)"
msgstr ""
"‘Others will be attached to their own views, holding them tight, and "
"refusing to let go, but here we will not be attached to our own views, not "
"holding them tight, but will let them go easily.’"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "mn8:12.46"
msgid "2. Cittupapādapariyāya"
msgstr "2. Giving Rise to the Thought"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc56"></a>
#. VAR: bahukāraṃ → bahūpakāraṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn8:13.1"
msgid ""
"Cittuppādampi kho ahaṃ, cunda, kusalesu dhammesu bahukāraṃ vadāmi, ko pana "
"vādo kāyena vācāya anuvidhīyanāsu."
msgstr ""
"Cunda, I say that even giving rise to the thought of skillful qualities is "
"very helpful, not to speak of following that path in body and speech."

msgctxt "mn8:13.2"
msgid ""
"Tasmātiha, cunda, ‘pare vihiṃsakā bhavissanti, mayamettha avihiṃsakā "
"bhavissāmā’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"That’s why you should give rise to the following thoughts. ‘Others will be "
"cruel, but here we will not be cruel.’"

msgctxt "mn8:13.3"
msgid ""
"‘Pare pāṇātipātī bhavissanti, mayamettha pāṇātipātā paṭiviratā bhavissāmā’ti "
"cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""
"‘Others will kill living creatures, but here we will not kill living "
"creatures.’ …"

msgctxt "mn8:13.4"
msgid ""
"‘pare sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggī bhavissanti, mayamettha "
"asandiṭṭhiparāmāsī anādhānaggāhī suppaṭinissaggī bhavissāmā’ti cittaṃ "
"uppādetabbaṃ. (44)"
msgstr ""
"‘Others will be attached to their own views, holding them tight, and "
"refusing to let go, but here we will not be attached to our own views, not "
"holding them tight, but will let them go easily.’"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "mn8:13.5"
msgid "3. Parikkamanapariyāya"
msgstr "3. A Way Around"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.44"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc57"></a>
#. VAR: assa, tassa → maggo tassāssa (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn8:14.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, cunda, visamo maggo assa, tassa añño samo maggo parikkamanāya;"
msgstr ""
"Cunda, suppose there was a rough path and another smooth path to get around "
"it."

msgctxt "mn8:14.2"
msgid ""
"seyyathā vā pana, cunda, visamaṃ titthaṃ assa, tassa aññaṃ samaṃ titthaṃ "
"parikkamanāya;"
msgstr ""
"Or suppose there was a rough ford and another smooth ford to get around it."

msgctxt "mn8:14.3"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, cunda, vihiṃsakassa purisapuggalassa avihiṃsā hoti "
"parikkamanāya, pāṇātipātissa purisapuggalassa pāṇātipātā veramaṇī hoti "
"parikkamanāya, adinnādāyissa purisapuggalassa adinnādānā veramaṇī hoti "
"parikkamanāya, abrahmacārissa purisapuggalassa abrahmacariyā veramaṇī hoti "
"parikkamanāya, musāvādissa purisapuggalassa musāvādā veramaṇī hoti "
"parikkamanāya, pisuṇavācassa purisapuggalassa pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇī hoti "
"parikkamanāya, pharusavācassa purisapuggalassa pharusāya vācāya veramaṇī "
"hoti parikkamanāya, samphappalāpissa purisapuggalassa samphappalāpā veramaṇī "
"hoti parikkamanāya, abhijjhālussa purisapuggalassa anabhijjhā hoti "
"parikkamanāya, byāpannacittassa purisapuggalassa abyāpādo hoti "
"parikkamanāya. (1–10.)"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a cruel individual gets around it by not being cruel. An "
"individual who kills gets around it by not killing. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc58"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:14.4"
msgid ""
"Micchādiṭṭhissa purisapuggalassa sammādiṭṭhi hoti parikkamanāya, "
"micchāsaṅkappassa purisapuggalassa sammāsaṅkappo hoti parikkamanāya, "
"micchāvācassa purisapuggalassa sammāvācā hoti parikkamanāya, "
"micchākammantassa purisapuggalassa sammākammanto hoti parikkamanāya, "
"micchāājīvassa purisapuggalassa sammāājīvo hoti parikkamanāya, "
"micchāvāyāmassa purisapuggalassa sammāvāyāmo hoti parikkamanāya, "
"micchāsatissa purisapuggalassa sammāsati hoti parikkamanāya, "
"micchāsamādhissa purisapuggalassa sammāsamādhi hoti parikkamanāya, "
"micchāñāṇissa purisapuggalassa sammāñāṇaṃ hoti parikkamanāya, "
"micchāvimuttissa purisapuggalassa sammāvimutti hoti parikkamanāya. (11–20.)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc59"></a>
#. VAR: amāyā → amāyāvitā (mr)
msgctxt "mn8:14.5"
msgid ""
"Thinamiddhapariyuṭṭhitassa purisapuggalassa vigatathinamiddhatā hoti "
"parikkamanāya, uddhatassa purisapuggalassa anuddhaccaṃ hoti parikkamanāya, "
"vicikicchissa purisapuggalassa tiṇṇavicikicchatā hoti parikkamanāya, "
"kodhanassa purisapuggalassa akkodho hoti parikkamanāya, upanāhissa "
"purisapuggalassa anupanāho hoti parikkamanāya, makkhissa purisapuggalassa "
"amakkho hoti parikkamanāya, paḷāsissa purisapuggalassa apaḷāso hoti "
"parikkamanāya, issukissa purisapuggalassa anissukitā hoti parikkamanāya, "
"maccharissa purisapuggalassa amacchariyaṃ hoti parikkamanāya, saṭhassa "
"purisapuggalassa asāṭheyyaṃ hoti parikkamanāya, māyāvissa purisapuggalassa "
"amāyā hoti parikkamanāya, thaddhassa purisapuggalassa atthaddhiyaṃ hoti "
"parikkamanāya, atimānissa purisapuggalassa anatimāno hoti parikkamanāya, "
"dubbacassa purisapuggalassa sovacassatā hoti parikkamanāya, pāpamittassa "
"purisapuggalassa kalyāṇamittatā hoti parikkamanāya, pamattassa "
"purisapuggalassa appamādo hoti parikkamanāya, assaddhassa purisapuggalassa "
"saddhā hoti parikkamanāya, ahirikassa purisapuggalassa hirī hoti "
"parikkamanāya, anottāpissa purisapuggalassa ottappaṃ hoti parikkamanāya, "
"appassutassa purisapuggalassa bāhusaccaṃ hoti parikkamanāya, kusītassa "
"purisapuggalassa vīriyārambho hoti parikkamanāya, muṭṭhassatissa "
"purisapuggalassa upaṭṭhitassatitā hoti parikkamanāya, duppaññassa "
"purisapuggalassa paññāsampadā hoti parikkamanāya, "
"sandiṭṭhiparāmāsiādhānaggāhiduppaṭinissaggissa purisapuggalassa "
"asandiṭṭhiparāmāsianādhānaggāhisuppaṭinissaggitā hoti parikkamanāya. (21–44.)"
msgstr ""
"An individual who is attached to their own views, holding them tight, and "
"refusing to let go, gets around it by not being attached to their own views, "
"not holding them tight, but letting them go easily."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "mn8:14.6"
msgid "4. Uparibhāgapariyāya"
msgstr "4. Going Up"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.45"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc60"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:15.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, cunda, ye keci akusalā dhammā sabbe te adhobhāgaṅgamanīyā, ye "
"keci kusalā dhammā sabbe te uparibhāgaṅgamanīyā;"
msgstr ""
"Cunda, all unskillful qualities lead downwards, while all skillful qualities "
"lead upwards."

#. VAR: uparibhāgāya → uparibhāvāya (bj, s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "mn8:15.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, cunda, vihiṃsakassa purisapuggalassa avihiṃsā hoti "
"uparibhāgāya, pāṇātipātissa purisapuggalassa pāṇātipātā veramaṇī hoti "
"uparibhāgāya … pe …"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a cruel individual is led upwards by not being cruel. An "
"individual who kills is led upwards by not killing …"

msgctxt "mn8:15.3"
msgid ""
"sandiṭṭhiparāmāsiādhānaggāhiduppaṭinissaggissa purisapuggalassa "
"asandiṭṭhiparāmāsianādhānaggāhisuppaṭinissaggitā hoti uparibhāgāya. (44)"
msgstr ""
"An individual who is attached to their own views, holding them tight, and "
"refusing to let go, is led upwards by not being attached to their own views, "
"not holding them tight, but letting them go easily."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "mn8:15.4"
msgid "5. Parinibbānapariyāya"
msgstr "5. The Exposition by Extinguishment"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya16"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc61"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:16.1"
msgid ""
"So vata, cunda, attanā palipapalipanno paraṃ palipapalipannaṃ uddharissatīti "
"netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"Truly, Cunda, if you’re sinking down in the mud you can’t pull out someone "
"else who is also sinking down in the mud."

msgctxt "mn8:16.2"
msgid ""
"So vata, cunda, attanā apalipapalipanno paraṃ palipapalipannaṃ "
"uddharissatīti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"But if you’re not sinking down in the mud you can pull out someone else who "
"is sinking down in the mud."

msgctxt "mn8:16.3"
msgid ""
"So vata, cunda, attanā adanto avinīto aparinibbuto paraṃ damessati vinessati "
"parinibbāpessatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"Truly, if you’re not tamed, trained, and extinguished you can’t tame, train, "
"and extinguish someone else."

msgctxt "mn8:16.4"
msgid ""
"So vata, cunda, attanā danto vinīto parinibbuto paraṃ damessati vinessati "
"parinibbāpessatīti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"But if you’re tamed, trained, and extinguished you can tame, train, and "
"extinguish someone else."

msgctxt "mn8:16.5"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, cunda, vihiṃsakassa purisapuggalassa avihiṃsā hoti "
"parinibbānāya, pāṇātipātissa purisapuggalassa pāṇātipātā veramaṇī hoti "
"parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a cruel individual extinguishes it by not being cruel. An "
"individual who kills extinguishes it by not killing. …"

msgctxt "mn8:16.6"
msgid "Adinnādāyissa purisapuggalassa adinnādānā veramaṇī hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.7"
msgid ""
"Abrahmacārissa purisapuggalassa abrahmacariyā veramaṇī hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.8"
msgid "Musāvādissa purisapuggalassa musāvādā veramaṇī hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.9"
msgid ""
"Pisuṇavācassa purisapuggalassa pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇī hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.10"
msgid ""
"Pharusavācassa purisapuggalassa pharusāya vācāya veramaṇī hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.11"
msgid ""
"Samphappalāpissa purisapuggalassa samphappalāpā veramaṇī hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.12"
msgid "Abhijjhālussa purisapuggalassa anabhijjhā hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.13"
msgid "Byāpannacittassa purisapuggalassa abyāpādo hoti parinibbānāya. (1–10.)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc62"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:16.14"
msgid "Micchādiṭṭhissa purisapuggalassa sammādiṭṭhi hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.15"
msgid "Micchāsaṅkappassa purisapuggalassa sammāsaṅkappo hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.16"
msgid "Micchāvācassa purisapuggalassa sammāvācā hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.17"
msgid "Micchākammantassa purisapuggalassa sammākammanto hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.18"
msgid "Micchāājīvassa purisapuggalassa sammāājīvo hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.19"
msgid "Micchāvāyāmassa purisapuggalassa sammāvāyāmo hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.20"
msgid "Micchāsatissa purisapuggalassa sammāsati hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.21"
msgid "Micchāsamādhissa purisapuggalassa sammāsamādhi hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.22"
msgid "Micchāñāṇissa purisapuggalassa sammāñāṇaṃ hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.23"
msgid ""
"Micchāvimuttissa purisapuggalassa sammāvimutti hoti parinibbānāya. (11–20.)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.46"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc63"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:16.24"
msgid ""
"Thinamiddhapariyuṭṭhitassa purisapuggalassa vigatathinamiddhatā hoti "
"parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.25"
msgid "Uddhatassa purisapuggalassa anuddhaccaṃ hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.26"
msgid "Vicikicchissa purisapuggalassa tiṇṇavicikicchatā hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.27"
msgid "Kodhanassa purisapuggalassa akkodho hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.28"
msgid "Upanāhissa purisapuggalassa anupanāho hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.29"
msgid "Makkhissa purisapuggalassa amakkho hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.30"
msgid "Paḷāsissa purisapuggalassa apaḷāso hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.31"
msgid "Issukissa purisapuggalassa anissukitā hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.32"
msgid "Maccharissa purisapuggalassa amacchariyaṃ hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.33"
msgid "Saṭhassa purisapuggalassa asāṭheyyaṃ hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.34"
msgid "Māyāvissa purisapuggalassa amāyā hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.35"
msgid "Thaddhassa purisapuggalassa atthaddhiyaṃ hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.36"
msgid "Atimānissa purisapuggalassa anatimāno hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.37"
msgid "Dubbacassa purisapuggalassa sovacassatā hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.38"
msgid "Pāpamittassa purisapuggalassa kalyāṇamittatā hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.39"
msgid "Pamattassa purisapuggalassa appamādo hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.40"
msgid "Assaddhassa purisapuggalassa saddhā hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.41"
msgid "Ahirikassa purisapuggalassa hirī hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.42"
msgid "Anottāpissa purisapuggalassa ottappaṃ hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.43"
msgid "Appassutassa purisapuggalassa bāhusaccaṃ hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.44"
msgid "Kusītassa purisapuggalassa vīriyārambho hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.45"
msgid "Muṭṭhassatissa purisapuggalassa upaṭṭhitassatitā hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.46"
msgid "Duppaññassa purisapuggalassa paññāsampadā hoti parinibbānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn8:16.47"
msgid ""
"Sandiṭṭhiparāmāsiādhānaggāhiduppaṭinissaggissa purisapuggalassa "
"asandiṭṭhiparāmāsianādhānaggāhisuppaṭinissaggitā hoti parinibbānāya. (21–44.)"
msgstr ""
"An individual who is attached to their own views, holding them tight, and "
"refusing to let go, extinguishes it by not being attached to their own "
"views, not holding them tight, but letting them go easily."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya17"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc64"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:17.1"
msgid ""
"Iti kho, cunda, desito mayā sallekhapariyāyo, desito cittuppādapariyāyo, "
"desito parikkamanapariyāyo, desito uparibhāgapariyāyo, desito "
"parinibbānapariyāyo."
msgstr ""
"So, Cunda, I’ve taught the expositions by way of self-effacement, giving "
"rise to thought, the way around, going up, and extinguishing."

msgctxt "mn8:17.2"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, cunda, satthārā karaṇīyaṃ sāvakānaṃ hitesinā anukampakena anukampaṃ "
"upādāya, kataṃ vo taṃ mayā."
msgstr ""
"Out of compassion, I’ve done what a teacher should do who wants what’s best "
"for their disciples."

msgctxt "mn8:17.3"
msgid ""
"Etāni, cunda, rukkhamūlāni, etāni suññāgārāni, jhāyatha, cunda, mā "
"pamādattha, mā pacchāvippaṭisārino ahuvattha—ayaṃ kho amhākaṃ anusāsanī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Here are these roots of trees, and here are these empty huts. Practice "
"absorption, Cunda! Don’t be negligent! Don’t regret it later! This is my "
"instruction.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc65"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:17.4"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn8:17.5"
msgid "Attamano āyasmā mahācundo bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti."
msgstr "Satisfied, Venerable Mahācunda was happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc66"></a>
msgctxt "mn8:17.6"
msgid "Catuttālīsapadā vuttā,"
msgstr "Forty-four items have been stated,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn8:17.7"
msgid "sandhayo pañca desitā;"
msgstr "organized into five sections."

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn8:17.8"
msgid "Sallekho nāma suttanto,"
msgstr "“Effacement” is the name of this discourse,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn8:17.9"
msgid "gambhīro sāgarūpamoti."
msgstr "which is deep as the ocean."

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn8:17.10"
msgid "Sallekhasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
